1.4.1.name: wordpress/capability-manager-enhanced
1.4.1.description:
Capability Manager plugin provides a simple way to manage WordPress role definitions (Subscriber, Editor, etc.) View or change the capabilities of any role, add new roles, copy existing roles into new ones, and add new capabilities to existing roles. You can also delegate capability management to other users. In this case, some restrictions apply to this users, as they can only set/unset the capabilities they have. With the Backup/Restore tool, you can save your Roles and Capabilities before making changes and revert them if something goes wrong. You'll find it on the Tools menu.

  • Only users with 'manage_capabilities' can manage them. This capability is created at install time and assigned to Administrators.
  • Administrator role cannot be deleted.
  • Non-administrators can only manage roles or users with same or lower capabilities.

Enhanced and supported by Kevin Behrens since July 2012. The original Capabil
